This set follows the classic fairytale of Goldilocks and the Three Bears, which teaches children the importance of respecting others' property and thinking about how their actions affect others.  These magnets act as a replacement for old felt boards, providing a sleeker look and a longer-lasting product.  Each magnet is laminated for longevity, and has a magnetic backing, perfect for use with  whiteboards and fridges. These magnets act as a replacement for old felt boards, providing a sleeker look and a longer-lasting product.  Each magnet is laminated for longevity, and has a magnetic backing, perfect for use with whiteboards and fridges.  This storyboard magnet set includes 13 magnets;  1x Goldilocks(13.5cm x 7cm)  1x baby bear (12.2cm x 7.4cm) 1x mama bear (15cm x 7.4cm) 1x papa bear (16cm x 8cm) 3x chairs (3 varying sizes+ designs) ( largest ~ 10cm x 5cm) 3x beds (3 varying sizes + designs) (largest ~ 14cm x 13cm) 3 x bowls of porridge (3 varying sizes and designs) (largest ~ 3.7cm x 4cm) The set comes with a story card booklet, which features an illustrated front cover and a colourful binding ring.  ***OPTIONAL STORAGE BAG**** There is also the option of adding a drawstring cotton storage bag to this order. results.description: This resource is a Goldilocks Drawing Characters Activity.Students will have 5 different pictures to choose from to practice drawing characters from the fairy tale.These pictures will be linked to a video for students to show them how to draw.There are 8 templates for students to draw and write.
results.grid_title: Goldilocks and the Three Bears | Drawing Characters Activity

rich_summary.display_description: Introducing a Goldilocks and the Three Bears Drawing Characters Activity for young students to practice illustrating scenes from the classic fairy tale. This teaching resource includes 5 character templates for tracing key figures like Goldilocks, Baby Bear, and Mama Bear. An accompanying video tutorial demonstrates simple techniques for sketching each character. With 8 pages for drawing and writing, this activity is ideal for independent practice, centers , or a follow-up to reading the story aloud. Use it to assess comprehension, spark discussion, or decorate the classroom. Applicable across preschool, kindergarten, 1st grade, and 2nd grade, this drawing packet brings a beloved story to life while building early literacy skills. Students will love recreating memorable moments from Goldilocks’ adventures in the three bears' house. Goldilocks and the Three Bears | Drawing Characters Activity
